          "guid": "mryeckrgkgpbfihq",
          "message": {
            "text": "Mutant-tested to confirm these guards have teeth: disabling the settle in\n`seekTo` (forcing the branch false) makes the **once-per-document** test fail.\n\nThe first test (immediate seek after `setContent`) still PASSED while mutated —\nthe underlying race is intermittent, so it cannot be a deterministic guard. It is\nkept because it asserts the actual user-visible contract and will catch a\nregression whenever the race manifests; the marker test is the deterministic one.\n\nField evidence: 7 full runs of the 8-file compressor e2e set (34 tests) produced\nno DM-1781-signature failure (strict caps, 1-2 regions, few hundred px).\n",
            "markdown": "Mutant-tested to confirm these guards have teeth: disabling the settle in\n`seekTo` (forcing the branch false) makes the **once-per-document** test fail.\n\nThe first test (immediate seek after `setContent`) still PASSED while mutated —\nthe underlying race is intermittent, so it cannot be a deterministic guard. It is\nkept because it asserts the actual user-visible contract and will catch a\nregression whenever the race manifests; the marker test is the deterministic one.\n\nField evidence: 7 full runs of the 8-file compressor e2e set (34 tests) produced\nno DM-1781-signature failure (strict caps, 1-2 regions, few hundred px).\n"
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "tests/seek-settle.e2e.test.ts"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 38,
                  "endLine": 56,
                  "snippet": {
                    "text": "  it(\"pauses and seeks every animation even when seeked immediately after setContent\", async () => {\n    const page = await browser.newPage();\n    // Deliberately NO settle here — reproducing the flake's exact conditions is\n    // the whole point, so the guard must not paper over it from the test side.\n    await page.setContent(HTML, { waitUntil: \"domcontentloaded\" });\n    await seekTo(page, 500);\n\n    const states = await page.evaluate(() =>\n      document.getAnimations().map((a) => ({ playState: a.playState, currentTime: Number(a.currentTime) })));\n\n    expect(states.length).toBe(2);\n    for (const s of states) {\n      expect(s.playState).toBe(\"paused\");\n      expect(s.currentTime).toBe(500);\n    }\n    await page.close();\n  });\n\n  it(\"settles once per DOCUMENT — and a fresh document settles again\", async () => {"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          ],
